    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A single-page scrolling layout is used for a narrative, intuitive user flow. It starts with a Hero section for immediate impact, followed by About/Values, an interactive Service Packages section with tabs and a dynamic comparison chart to simplify decision-making, a 'Why Us' section using icons for scannability, and a final Contact section. This structure guides the user from awareness to consideration and action, which is more effective for a corporate profile than a simple document layout. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: The core interaction is the service tier comparison. Report Info: Tiered packages table. Goal: Compare services & price. Viz/Presentation: A matrix table allows direct feature-by-feature comparison across tiers. Feature descriptions are now tooltips on the feature names to compress the table. Justification: This provides a comprehensive overview, making all information accessible while optimizing for space. Library/Method: Vanilla JS for DOM manipulation and table generation. Other sections use Tailwind grids and flexbox with icons for clear, scannable information. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
